Space complexity = constant OR 1; anything less than n is considered as constant
Considering input array length = n
Considering feed for binary search is of length.= m [10------32] 
Time Complexity = O(n) + O(log m) * n
	Explaination: 
		```log For the first O(n) it is because of iterating over nums array to get max and sum.
		For the second O(log m) * n is because binary search over low and high AND in each iteration we iterate over n items. ```log
Please feel free to correct the explainations or any mistakes so done.


