**Solution 1: DP (Time: O(m*n^2); Space: O(m*n))**

```
class Solution {
    public int splitArray(int[] nums, int m) {

        int n = nums.length;
        int[][] dp = new int[m+1][n+1];

        for (int j = 1; j <= n; j++)
            dp[1][j] = dp[1][j-1] + nums[j-1]; // Increasing sum array

        for (int i = 2; i <= m; i++)
        {
            for (int j = 1; j <= n; j++)
            {
                dp[i][j] = Integer.MAX_VALUE;

                // Suppose the first k numbers have been splitted into i-1 subarrays
                // We just need to check if the sum of the ith subarray is larger than the former subarrays or not
                for (int k = 1; k < j; k++)
                    dp[i][j] = Math.min(dp[i][j], Math.max(dp[i-1][k], dp[1][j] - dp[1][k]));
            }
        }

        return dp[m][n];
    }
}
```


**Solution 2: Binary Search (Time: O(n*logk) where k equals (sum-max), beats 100%; Space: O(1))**

```
class Solution {
    public int splitArray(int[] nums, int m) {

        int sum = 0, max = 0;

        for (int num : nums)
        {
            sum += num;
            max = Math.max(max, num);
        }

        int left = max, right = sum;

        while (left <= right)
        {
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;

            if (valid(nums, m, mid))
                right = mid - 1;
            else
                left = mid + 1;
        }

        return left;
    }

    // Check if the numbers can be splitted into m subarrays and each subarray subSum <= target
    private boolean valid(int[] nums, int m, int target)
    {
        int subSum = 0, count = 0;

        for (int num : nums)
        {
            subSum += num;

            if (subSum > target)
            {
                count++;
                subSum = num;

                if (count > m)
                    return false;
            }
        }

        return (subSum > 0 && count == m) ? false : true;
    }
}
